This paper deals with communication protocols and scheduling algorithms in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of information theory to improve the reliability of communication, which suggests a possible fit with the information theory subcategory (cs.IT). The proposed solution involves coordination and decision-making among multiple entities, which could be classified under the systems and control subcategory (cs.SY). The paper also addresses security concerns related to message collisions, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security subcategory (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the proposed solution on future applications such as autonomous driving, which suggests a possible fit with the multimedia subcategory (cs.MM).
